THE REVISION OF THE LAWS ORDER, 1980
1. This Order may be cited as the Revision of the Laws Order, 1980.
2. The tenth annual supplement to the Laws of Kenya prepared under section 7 of the Act shall come into force on the 17th Novem­ber, 1980.
DIRECTIONS FOR USE OF NEW SUPPLEMENT
1. The tenth annual supplement comprises the following booklets­
(a) chapters 1, 250, 259, 441, 442, 472 and 505 which are incorporated in the Laws of Kenya for the first time; (b) 39 new revised chapters, namely nos. 6, 10, 11, 12, 13, 15, 17, 18, 34, 41, 104, 105, 111, 122, 154, 189, 190, 193, 199, 202, 204, 211, 222, 229, 234, 254, 285, 318, 323, 359, 366, 394, 412, 461, 475, 478, 484, 497 and 502;
(c) a new revised accumulative index containing a complete noter up of the Laws of Kenya as at the 1st January, 1980, and including a supplement to the chronological table;
(d) a new revised table of contents, including a separate table of omitted Acts,
which should be inserted in appropriate numerical sequence in the volumes of the Laws.
2. As a the new booklets are inserted into the volumes the following booklets should be removed and stored for future reference -
(a) chapters 1 and 505 which have been repealed and re­placed;
(b) chapters 6, 10, 11, 12, 13, 15, 17, 18, 34, 41, 104, 105 111, 122, 154, 189, 190, 193, 199, 202, 204, 211, 222, 229, 234, 254, 285, 318, 328, 359, 366, 394, 412, 461, 475, 478, 484, 497 and 502, which have been newly revised;
(c) the old table of contents and index.
3. The Government Printer will supply the 1980 supplement com­plete to persons not entitled to free supplements at a total cost of Sh. 910.
4. The opportunity should also be taken when inserting and extracting booklets to check whether each set of the laws is up to date. This can be done in the following manner­
(a) check that the contents of the thirteen volumes tally with the 1980 edition of the table of contents supplied as part of - the 1980 supplement (the actual chapters in each individual volume should be within the range of chapter numbers speci­field on the card printed in red on the spine);
(b) any chapters not specified in the 1980 edition of the table of contents will be found to contain laws which have been repealed or replaced or become spent and should be removed from the volumes;
(c) once the chapters have been checked against the table of contents reference should then be made to the index to check that each chapter is the latest, and therefore the current, edition; the year of last revision is printed in the third column of Part I of the index.Where chapters are found to be missing, or to be outdated editions, replacements should be ordered from the Government Printer.

THE REVISION OF THE LAWS ORDER, 1981
1. This Order may be cited as the Revision of the Laws Order, 1981.
2. The eleventh annual supplement to the Laws of Kenya prepared under section 7 of the Act shall come into force on the 25th May, 1981.
DIRECTION FOR USE OF NEW SUPPLEMENT
1. The eleventh annual supplement comprises the following book­lets which should be inserted in appropriate sequence in the volumes of the Laws­
(a) chapters 70, 160, 209, 225n, 472 (second booklet) and 473, which are incorporated in the Laws of Kenya for the first time;
(b) 21 new revised chapters, namely nos. 24, 26, 27, 28, 29, 30, 31, 32, 40, 64, 65, 67, 102, 103, 109, 164, 302, 476, 488, 496 and 518;
(c) a new revised accumulative index containing a complete noter­up of the Laws of Kenya as at the 1st January, 1981, and including a supplement to the chronological table;
(d) a new revised table of contents, including a separate table of omitted Acts.
2. As the new booklets are inserted into the volumes the follow­ing booklets should be removed and stored for future reference­(a) chapter 495 which has been repealed;
(b) chapter 286 which has been newly revised and re-published with a new number;
(c) chapters 24, 26, 27, 28, 29, 30, 31, 32, 40, 64, 65, 67, 102, 103, 109, 302, 476, 488, 496 and 518, which have been newly revised;
(d) the old table of contents and index.
3. The Government Printer will supply the 1981 supplement complete to persons not entitled to free supplements at a total cost of Sh. 405.
4. The opportunity should also be taken when inserting and extracting booklets to check- whether each set -of the Laws is -up to date. This can be done in the following manner­
(a) check that the contents of the thirteen volumes tally with the 1981 edition of the table of contents supplied as part of the 1981 supplement (the actual chapters in each- individual volume should be within the range of chapter numbers specified on the card printed in red on the spine);
(b) any chapters not specified in the 1981 edition of the table of contents will be found- to contain laws which have been - repealed or replaced or become spent and should be removed from the volumes;
(c) once the chapters have been . checked against the table of contents reference should then be made to the index to check - that each chapter is the latest, and therefore the current, edition; the year of last revision is printed in the third column of Part I of the index.5. Where chapters are found to be missing, or to be outdated editions, replacements should be ordered from the Government Printer.

2. In this Act -
"annual supplement"
means a supplement prepared under section 7;
"foreign legislation" includes Acts of Parliament of the United Kingdom, Orders in Council, Royal Instructions, and subsidiary legislation made thereunder, and Acts of the Indian Legislature and subsidiary legislation made thereunder;
"Laws of Kenya" means the revised edition of the Laws of Kenya prepared and published under the Laws of Kenya (Revision) Act (now repealed).

4. The Laws of Kenya shall contain -
(a) the Constitution;
(b) all Acts in force, wholly or in part, unless omitted under section 5;
(c) such subsidiary legislation in force as the Attorney-General thinks fit to include therein;
(d) such foreign legislation which has been applied to Kenya as the Attorney-General thinks fit to include therein;
(e) a table of contents;
(f) a chronological table listing all Acts, Acts and other enactments ever enacted in Kenya and showing how such have been dealt with;
(g) an accumulative alphabetical index of all Acts, listing under each Act reference to -
(i) all subsidiary legislation made under it since the date of last revision of the Act or, in the case of an Act which has not been revised, the date of publication of the Act; and
(ii) all amendments to the Act and to any subsidiary legislation made thereunder since the date of the last revision of the Act, or since the date of publication of the Act or of the subsidiary legislation, as the case may be;
(h) a table of Acts omitted under the authority of paragraphs (b), (c), (d) or (e) of section 5, which table may be published either separately or annexed to the table of contents.

